-- Brazil’s BNDES May Lend 2.1 Billion Reais to Fiat, Folha Says
-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 2012-03-03T16:14:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/brazil-s-bndes-may-lend-2-1-billion-reais-to-fiat-folha-says.html
Brazil’s development bank  may lend
as much as 2.1 billion reais ($1.2 billion) to  Fiat SpA (F)  to build
a car plant in Pernambuco state, Folha de S.Paulo reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Fiat said it’s seeking financing with BNDES, as the state-
controlled lender is known, according to the  newspaper . The
company said it can’t provide details while negotiating with the
bank, Folha said.  BNDES declined to comment, citing secrecy agreements,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in  Sao Paulo  at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joe Sabo at 
 jsabo@bloomberg.net . 